1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a novel error correction coding scheme for AWGN channels, which is a core topic in information theory. 
2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The proposed scheme utilizes a special autoencoder, which is a type of neural network. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a deep learning-based error correction coding scheme, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with designing a coding scheme for a communication system, which can be considered as a control problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the bandwidth efficiency of the proposed coding scheme, which is relevant to multimedia applications.
